<table width="600">
	<tr>
		<td>
			<h1 align="center">Common Visual Interface in QBE</h1>
			<hr>			
		
			<p>
			<b>Tabular, form based:</b><br>
			In tabular or form based QBE, user puts values in tables or form to formulate their query. 
			</p>
			<div align="center">
			<i>Fig 1a. Examples of tabular QBE</i><br>
			<table border="1" width="42%" id="table1" style="border-collapse: collapse" bordercolor="#000000">
				<tr>
					<td width="53" align="center"><i>Sailors</i></td>
					<td width="36" align="center"><i>sid</i></td>
					<td width="55" align="center"><i>sname</i></td>
					<td width="50" align="center"><i>rating</i></td>
					<td align="center"><i>age</i></td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td width="53">P.</td>
					<td width="36">&nbsp;</td>
					<td width="55">&nbsp;</td>
					<td width="50">10</td>
					<td>&nbsp;</td>
				</tr>
			</table>
			</div>
			
			<p align="center">
			<br>
			<i>Fig 1b. Example of a form-based QBE</i><br>
			<img border="0" src="images/qbe-form-based.gif" width="539" height="412"><br>
			</p>
			
			<p>
			<b>Graph based:</b><br>
			In graph based QBE, user typically have a canvas window and a toolbar in which user can construct a query graph.
			</p>
			<p align="center">
			<i>Fig 2. Example of graph-based QBE</i><br>
			<img border="0" src="images/qbe-graph-based.GIF" width="482" height="398">
			</p>
			
			<p>
			<b>Symbolic Image, Sketch Based:</b><br>
			In symbolic image based QUE, user can drag and drop symbolic images onto a canvas to formulate their query.  In sketch based QUE, user can use drawing tools provided by the program to sketch the query he or she wants.
			</p>
			<p align="center">
			<i>Fig 3. Example of symbolicimage and sketch based QBE</i><br>
			<img border="0" src="images/imagescape/imagescape.jpg" width="697" height="527">
			</p>
			
			<p>
			<b>Object Based:</b><br>
			In object based QUE, user uploads an exmple image, audio, or video to the system in which features are extracted from the uploaded media to find object similar to the media.
			</p>

		</td>
	</tr>
</table>
